ropshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Powys, Wales":"Powys, Wales, United Kingdom"},"da":{"Abt 1110–about 1171":"omkring 1110–omkring 1171","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1090–Female":"1090–Afdød","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1047–1132":"1047–1132","1050–Female":"1050–Afdød","1090":"1090","about 1171":"omkring 1171","9 February 1132":"9. februar 1132","1132":"1132","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1050":"1050","1171":"1171","1047":"1047","Abt 1110":"omkring 1110","1221":"1221","1100":"1100","Cae Howel, Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Powys, Wales":"Powys, Wales, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"Abt 1110–about 1171":"circa 1110–circa 1171","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1090–Female":"1090–Overleden","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1047–1132":"1047–1132","1050–Female":"1050–Overleden","1090":"1090","about 1171":"circa 1171","9 February 1132":"9 februari 1132","1132":"1132","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1050":"1050","1171":"1171","1047":"1047","Abt 1110":"circa 1110","1221":"1221","1100":"1100","Cae Howel, Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Powys, Wales":"Powys, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1110–about 1171":"about 1110–about 1171","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1090–Female":"1090–Deceased","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1047–1132":"1047–1132","1050–Female":"1050–Deceased","1090":"1090","about 1171":"about 1171","9 February 1132":"9 February 1132","1132":"1132","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1050":"1050","1171":"1171","1047":"1047","Abt 1110":"about 1110","1221":"1221","1100":"1100","Cae Howel, Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Powys, Wales":"Powys, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Goch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Polish Pawel, Zuzanna, Zygmunt.","North German: habitational name from any of various minor places which get their names from an ancient Germanic element <i>goch</i>, <i>gog</i> ‘marsh, bog, fen’.","Polish: from a pet form of various personal names beginning with <i>Go-</i>, such as <i>Gościsław</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Gotch","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>coch</i>, <i>goch</i> ‘red(-haired)’; see   Gooch   3.","English (Northamptonshire): variant of   Gooch   1 and 2.","Americanized form of German <b>Götsch</b> (see   Gotsch  )."]}]},{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Geza, Jeno, Arpad, Attila, Csaba.","Hungarian: variant of   Papp  , meaning ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’. This surname is also found in Romania, Slovakia, Croatia, and Serbia, and also among Rusyns (in Serbia and Croatia). See also   Pop   2 and   Popa  .","English: variant of   Pape   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Papp","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]},{"name":"Iorwerth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: from <i>iōr</i>‘ ‘lord’ + a mutated form of <i>berth</i> ‘handsome’; borne in the <i>Mabinogi</i> by the jealous brother of  Madawg , son of  Maredudd . <i>Iorwerth</i> came to be regarded as a Welsh equivalent of  Edward , but it has no actual connection with that name."],"variants":[{"name":"Yorath","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Iorwerth   or, in some cases, a transferred use of the surname derived from it."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Iorwerth Goch ap Maredudd was born about 1110, in Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Maredudd ap Bleddyn Prince of Powys, was 64 and his mother, Cristin ferch Bledrus, was 62. He had at least 1 son with Maud de Manley. He died about 1171, at the age of 63."},"et":{"Abt 1110–about 1171":"umbes 1110–umbes 1171","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1090–Female":"1090–Surnud","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1047–1132":"1047–1132","1050–Female":"1050–Surnud","1090":"1090","about 1171":"umbes 1171","9 February 1132":"9. veebruar 1132","1132":"1132","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1050":"1050","1171":"1171","1047":"1047","Abt 1110":"umbes 1110","1221":"1221","1100":"1100","Cae Howel, Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Powys, Wales":"Powys, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1110–about 1171":"noin 1110–noin 1171","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1090–Female":"1090–Kuollut","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1047–1132":"1047–1132","1050–Female":"1050–Kuollut","1090":"1090","about 1171":"noin 1171","9 February 1132":"9. helmikuuta 1132","1132":"1132","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1050":"1050","1171":"1171","1047":"1047","Abt 1110":"noin 1110","1221":"1221","1100":"1100","Cae Howel, Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",